            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H1" QuickReferenceTitle="Dialog" class="scroll-mt-20">Dialog</RzHeading>
            <RzParagraph>
                The RzDialog component suite provides a flexible way to display modal dialogs. It's a composable system built from components like <code>DialogTrigger</code>, <code>DialogContent</code>, <code>DialogHeader</code>, and more. It leverages Alpine.js for client-side state management, transitions, focus trapping, and standard closing mechanisms. Its internal body and footer areas have stable IDs, allowing HTMX to dynamically load or update content within the dialog after it's opened.
            </RzParagraph>

            <RzAlert Variant="ThemeVariant.Information" class="mb-6">
                <AlertTitle>Under the Hood</AlertTitle>
                <AlertDescription>
                    This component uses an Alpine.js component (<code>x-data="rzModal"</code>) to manage its state and interactions. It utilizes <code>&lt;template x-teleport="body"&gt;</code> to ensure the dialog is rendered at the end of the document body, avoiding potential z-index issues.
                </AlertDescription>
            </RzAlert>

